Application Folder
        |
        |-----> WEB-INF
        |           |
        |           |-------->  Classes :   contains servlets classes
        |           |
        |           |-------->  lib  : external libraries for servlets, spring     
        |           |
        |           |--------> web.xml: contains mapping data.  -> with this servlet container will understand
        |                                                          for which file which servlet class is required
        |
        |-----> View Resources : html , css, javascript                 
        
        


If i put this whole Application folder in tomcat container  is in root folder
Now if you start the server, it will first read web.xml file, and read all the mappings

After Servlet 3, web.xml is not required.
you can use anotations

